        "last_activity_date": 1475354923,
        "creation_date": 1475349646,
        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "How to figure out which value is 0?",
        "body": "<p>I got my 1st crash report for my app. It says there is a <code>java.lang.ArithmeticException: divide by zero<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>The exception is on one of these two lines: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>//sWP stands for \"Screen Width in Pixels\"\n// sW stands for \"Screen Width\" The code is old though, so I may be incorrect for both variables.\n//res is just getResources()\nint sWP = sW / (res.getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi / DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT);\nfloat bHeight = 50 * ((float)res.getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi / DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Can <code>DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT<\/code> ever be zero? Or can <code>getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi<\/code> ever be zero? <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 39810599,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "android",
            "android-5.0-lollipop",
            "arithmeticexception",
            "dividebyzeroexception"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "is_answered": false,
        "view_count": 67
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d7ca37cecc22478442992b26949ba01f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
            "account_id": 9303760,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 6908279,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6908279/m-s",
            "reputation": 322,
            "display_name": "M.S."
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 0,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1475354923,
        "creation_date": 1475351302,
        "body": "<p><code>res.getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi<\/code> will be 120, 160 or 240 (or something similar), see <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/DisplayMetrics.html#densityDpi\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/DisplayMetrics.html#densityDpi<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p><code>DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT<\/code> constantly equals 160, see <a href=\"https://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/DisplayMetrics.html#DENSITY_DEFAULT\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/DisplayMetrics.html#DENSITY_DEFAULT<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p><code>res.getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi / DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT<\/code> will return 0 because you divide int by int.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Change the first of the two lines to<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p><code>int sWP = (int) sW / (((double) res.getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi) / DisplayMetrics.DENSITY_DEFAULT);<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p><strong>and it should work.<\/strong><\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 39810826,
        "question_id": 39810599,
        "last_edit_date": 1475354923
    }],
